[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "62af82bb51231f08a23c37388a6ab671aea54b3ca0f0a0b14b3533e40b2905b2"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has a pretty normal preemptive 3\D bid.

WEST has the equivalent of an opening 1NT bid and will be very tempted to bid 3NT.

That might turn out to be a disaster, particularly if WEST is unable to reach the EAST hand.

WEST should assume EAST can win six tricks if 
\Ds are trumps. Thinking this way points WEST to her 
best call - PASS.}

